The paper deals with optimization of communication systems, specifically the sum capacity of a MIMO cognitive radio channel. This falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms and techniques for achieving this optimization, which could fall under the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of cognitive radio technology and the need for adaptive algorithms could also place this paper in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper mentions the use of interior point techniques, which are commonly used in optimization problems in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
